WEBVTT

00:14.158 --> 00:15.867
(GURGUNG)

00:15.868 --> 00:19.018
<i>MAN: Shane, it's time to go.</i>

00:19.108 --> 00:23.789
<i>We'll be together again soon, mate,
don't you worry.</i>

00:32.879 --> 00:35.039
(HORNS BLARING)

00:35.129 --> 00:37.199
(CAR ALARM BUZZING)

00:37.289 --> 00:43.289
(POLICE SIREN WAILING)

01:07.711 --> 01:10.681
MAN: Wait till you see this joint.

01:10.770 --> 01:16.770
Nobody knows about it.

01:17.161 --> 01:22.202
- This is the best kept secret in New York.
- Really?

01:22.292 --> 01:28.231
You know, I'm gonna make some money,
trust me.

01:28.322 --> 01:30.322
This is where it's at.

01:30.392 --> 01:33.002
(CLUB MUSIC PLAYING)

01:33.091 --> 01:34.621
(TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

01:34.622 --> 01:40.622
(CROWD CHEERING)

02:20.255 --> 02:22.053
How are the numbers tonight?

02:22.054 --> 02:23.494
Better than ever.

02:23.495 --> 02:29.495
Goody.

02:35.195 --> 02:41.195
(CHEERING)

02:53.376 --> 02:59.376
CROWD: Oh!

03:20.287 --> 03:26.287
CROWD: Fight, fight, fight!

03:34.418 --> 03:40.418
(CROWD GROANING)

03:42.968 --> 03:48.968
(CHUCKLES)

04:14.200 --> 04:16.450
SCOTTY: Hey, Danny, hey!

04:16.540 --> 04:22.031
Screw you, man!

04:22.120 --> 04:26.081
Get that prick!

04:26.171 --> 04:28.150
- You scratch it, I scratch you.
- Move, move, move!

04:28.151 --> 04:33.641
Hey!

04:33.730 --> 04:36.161
No, no, no. This is yourfault.

04:36.251 --> 04:37.960
(TIRES SCREECHING)

04:37.961 --> 04:43.961
Get my car back, or I'm gonna get you back.

05:25.213 --> 05:27.733
One move and you're dead.

05:27.824 --> 05:29.443
(LAUGHS) Oh, Shane.

05:29.444 --> 05:33.043
Shane. God.

05:33.134 --> 05:35.384
What the hell, Scotty?
I almost took your freaking head off.

05:35.473 --> 05:39.344
Yeah, right. You could try, man.

05:39.434 --> 05:40.873
Hey, that's my bat.

05:40.874 --> 05:42.133
No, it ain't, it used to be.

05:42.134 --> 05:46.634
You gave it to James, remember?

05:46.724 --> 05:52.215
Never mind. You look like shit.

05:52.305 --> 05:54.014
They're all rough nights for you.

05:54.015 --> 06:00.015
Anyway, look, I only got a couple of minutes.

06:00.585 --> 06:02.024
What's this?

06:02.025 --> 06:05.805
Just paying you back. You know,
for all those times you helped me out?

06:05.895 --> 06:08.956
Plus, there's a little extra in there for...

06:09.045 --> 06:13.185
You know, being my big brother, man.

06:13.276 --> 06:15.615
So what do you want, Scotty?

06:15.706 --> 06:19.576
What? I don't want nothing.
ljust feel good, you know?

06:19.666 --> 06:22.997
Don't lie to me. I told you not to
come around here when you're high.

06:23.086 --> 06:27.856
Ah, God. "When you're high."

06:27.947 --> 06:32.176
Tell me something, Shane,
you ever feel high anymore?

06:32.266 --> 06:35.867
Busting your ass all day
fixing other people's cars, huh?

06:35.956 --> 06:38.927
Better than getting my brains beat out
for scum like Danny G.

06:39.017 --> 06:41.357
I'm not saying what you have here ain't great,
it is.

06:41.447 --> 06:45.857
You got a family, made a life for yourself.

06:45.947 --> 06:48.017
Slavin's Auto Repair?

06:48.107 --> 06:49.817
That's not me, man.

06:49.818 --> 06:51.256
Could be.

06:51.257 --> 06:53.147
Make an honest living for a change.

06:53.148 --> 06:55.127
Yeah, no thanks.

06:55.128 --> 06:57.107
Anyway, I got bigger plans.

06:57.108 --> 07:01.068
I'm gonna go to Reno with the rest of this,
and start up my own operation.

07:01.158 --> 07:03.588
What do you think, huh?

07:03.678 --> 07:05.387
You left Danny G?

07:05.388 --> 07:06.557
He let you go?

07:06.558 --> 07:08.808
Yeah. Yeah, sure, why not? He let you go.

07:08.899 --> 07:12.139
Not with money like that.

07:12.229 --> 07:15.649
You run out on him?

07:15.738 --> 07:18.259
Shane, ljust came over
to say goodbye, okay?

07:18.349 --> 07:21.139
S0, look, say hey to Connie and the kid
for me,

07:21.229 --> 07:24.199
and I'll see you in...

07:24.289 --> 07:26.289
Look, I'm gonna take the back door, okay?

07:26.360 --> 07:28.069
It's a long story.

07:28.070 --> 07:30.410
S0, catch you later on, bro.

07:30.500 --> 07:32.479
Hey, Scotty.

07:32.480 --> 07:38.480
Wait up.

07:39.590 --> 07:43.010
Take this. I don't need it.

07:43.100 --> 07:46.160
Scotty.

07:46.251 --> 07:51.830
Take it.
Wherever you end up, you're gonna need it.

07:51.921 --> 07:53.991
(LAUGHS SHEEPISHLY)

07:54.081 --> 08:00.081
Thanks, bro.

08:03.711 --> 08:09.711
Hey, catch you on the flip side, huh?

08:10.371 --> 08:16.371
(SIGHS)

08:18.382 --> 08:24.382
(GRUNTS)

08:42.773 --> 08:48.773
Get the money.

08:55.553 --> 08:56.903
Shit.

08:56.904 --> 08:59.064
Danny, we done here?

08:59.154 --> 09:05.154
For now.

09:32.636 --> 09:36.686
SHANE: I don't even know why I worry.
He's never gonna change.

09:36.776 --> 09:40.285
Of course you care, Shane,
he's still your brother.

09:40.376 --> 09:42.175
Yeah, but it's his life.

09:42.176 --> 09:45.056
He's like, what, 28 now?

09:45.146 --> 09:49.916
It's about time he learned
to take care of himself.

09:50.006 --> 09:51.985
Well, that's not my problem.

09:51.986 --> 09:57.986
- Mom, gonna be late for school.
- Okay.

10:05.127 --> 10:09.538
Ah, what did I tell you about all that sugar?

10:09.628 --> 10:12.237
Was Uncle Scotty here last night?

10:12.327 --> 10:14.327
What makes you think
Uncle Scotty was here last night?

10:14.397 --> 10:17.368
Duh.

10:17.458 --> 10:19.528
Yeah, he was here, but he couldn't stay.

10:19.617 --> 10:22.948
But he told me to tell you that he misses you
and he can't wait to see you.

10:23.038 --> 10:24.837
So how's that project of yours coming along?

10:24.838 --> 10:27.718
Have you figured
out how to make that water mill work?

10:27.809 --> 10:29.068
What?

10:29.069 --> 10:30.507
Is there a problem?

10:30.508 --> 10:33.569
He had a run-in with some kids at school.

10:33.659 --> 10:35.188
What kind of a run-in?

10:35.189 --> 10:39.958
Well, he brought his project in
to show the teacher,

10:40.049 --> 10:43.198
Did your teacher see what these kids did?

10:43.289 --> 10:45.088
No.

10:45.089 --> 10:47.879
And I have to start all over.

10:47.969 --> 10:50.489
Ijust wanna kill them.

10:50.580 --> 10:52.468
But you're not gonna, right?

10:52.469 --> 10:54.359
Because you're smarter than that.

10:54.360 --> 10:56.068
I don't wanna be smart.

10:56.069 --> 11:02.069
I wanna be strong like you
and kick their asses.

11:03.810 --> 11:08.310
Well, guess what, buddy?

11:08.401 --> 11:13.530
You are gonna kick their asses,

11:13.620 --> 11:15.620
'Cause you know what fighting gets you?

11:15.690 --> 11:19.561
More fighting and more fighting,
until you're old and tired.

11:19.650 --> 11:21.901
And then someone
who's younger and stronger comes along

11:21.991 --> 11:24.421
and they beat the snot out of you.

11:24.511 --> 11:27.571
And then you're right back where you started,
which is where?

11:27.661 --> 11:29.280
Nowhere.

11:29.281 --> 11:30.900
That's right.

11:30.901 --> 11:35.222
So you stick to your books
and you remember,

11:35.312 --> 11:37.382
They're gonna be working for you one day.

11:37.471 --> 11:41.342
They're gonna want to be you.

11:41.432 --> 11:44.132
Okay.

11:44.222 --> 11:46.742
Hey.

11:46.832 --> 11:48.992
Look what I got for you.

11:49.082 --> 11:50.341
I knew you wanted one.

11:50.342 --> 11:53.852
Cool!

11:53.943 --> 11:56.733
- Go check that out.
- Thanks. Thanks, Dad!

11:56.823 --> 11:58.823
You're welcome.

11:58.893 --> 12:04.203
You are a handsome devil,
you take after your old man.

12:04.293 --> 12:06.002
<i>HEY,</i>

12:06.003 --> 12:09.153
I gotta go pick up
some parts that I ordered. Um...

12:09.243 --> 12:10.953
You want me to take him to school?

12:10.954 --> 12:12.954
No, we got lots of time.

12:13.024 --> 12:14.552
Hey.

12:14.553 --> 12:16.553
You're pretty smart yourself, you know that?

12:16.624 --> 12:17.973
Oh, yeah.

12:17.974 --> 12:23.974
I'm the man with all the answers.

12:32.915 --> 12:34.353
Jamesy.

12:34.354 --> 12:36.605
SHANE: Connie!

12:36.694 --> 12:38.224
Connie!

12:38.225 --> 12:41.555
Stay here.

12:41.645 --> 12:43.645
Oh, my God.

12:43.715 --> 12:46.234
Oh, my God. Oh, my God, is he okay?

12:46.325 --> 12:48.124
- Call an ambulance.
- Okay.

12:48.125 --> 12:54.125
Quickly, huh?

12:54.335 --> 13:00.335
What the hell have you gotten yourself into?

13:12.606 --> 13:17.107
Well?

13:17.197 --> 13:20.347
(SIGHS)

13:20.437 --> 13:22.146
He'll live.

13:22.147 --> 13:26.377
He's got a fractured radius,
three cracked ribs, broken nose,

13:26.467 --> 13:29.077
and some ligament damage.

13:29.167 --> 13:35.167
I'm so sorry, honey.

13:36.907 --> 13:40.507
He seems pretty convinced
that those guys were trying to kill him.

13:40.597 --> 13:42.938
You mean this Danny G
that you've been talking about?

13:43.027 --> 13:45.027
Yeah.

13:45.097 --> 13:47.438
It seems like he didn't take a dive in a fight
where he was supposed to,

13:47.528 --> 13:51.398
as well as running out on him.

13:51.488 --> 13:54.818
You know, he chose to live in this world.

13:54.909 --> 13:57.968
It can get pretty rough.

13:58.058 --> 14:01.119
How much money are we talking about?

14:01.208 --> 14:03.008
I have no idea, actually.

14:03.009 --> 14:06.519
But whatever it is, he doesn't have it.

14:06.608 --> 14:10.300
What's he gonna do?

14:10.389 --> 14:16.149
What are we gonna do?

14:16.239 --> 14:21.820
I guess we'll just lie low for a while.

14:21.910 --> 14:26.770
Look, I gotta get back to work.

14:26.860 --> 14:29.380
- You okay with James?
- Of course.

14:29.470 --> 14:35.470
Don't worry, okay?

14:35.590 --> 14:41.590
I love you. I'll talk to you later.

14:55.032 --> 14:56.561
FRANK: Hey.

14:56.562 --> 14:58.090
- Hey, Frank.
- How you doing?

14:58.091 --> 15:02.141
What's up?

15:02.231 --> 15:04.842
You Okay?

15:04.932 --> 15:06.371
Yeah, I'm fine, why?

15:06.372 --> 15:09.252
You seem kind of quiet
these last couple days.

15:09.342 --> 15:10.691
I'm good.

15:10.692 --> 15:12.491
Okay, well, uh...

15:12.492 --> 15:14.111
Anyways, I got a guy out front.

15:14.112 --> 15:18.973
Said he wants to talk to you
about a fractured radius?

15:19.063 --> 15:24.823
I don't... I don't even know what that is.

15:24.912 --> 15:26.912
You want me to handle this?

15:26.982 --> 15:29.053
No.

15:29.143 --> 15:35.143
- I've got it. You wait here.
- All right.

15:36.613 --> 15:38.232
Shane.

15:38.233 --> 15:41.113
Long time. You got a minute?

15:41.203 --> 15:42.732
Danny wants to talk to you.

15:42.733 --> 15:44.173
Kind of busy right now.

15:44.174 --> 15:47.324
Not too busy to talk to Danny, are you?

15:47.414 --> 15:49.213
I've got nothing to say to him.

15:49.214 --> 15:52.185
You sure?
Maybe you two could talk about the old days.

15:52.274 --> 15:53.713
Reminisce and stuff.

15:53.714 --> 15:59.714
Look, I don't want any trouble.

16:21.166 --> 16:23.166
(BOTH GRUNTING)

16:23.236 --> 16:29.236
Ahh!

16:29.806 --> 16:33.046
(GROANS)

16:33.136 --> 16:39.136
DANNY G:
Tell your boy to put the phone down.

16:48.347 --> 16:50.867
I got business to discuss.

16:50.957 --> 16:55.097
So as you may have well heard by now,
I got a little problem with your brother.

16:55.187 --> 16:59.688
I don't know anything about
what goes on with you and Scotty.

16:59.777 --> 17:05.718
I know the room number,

17:05.808 --> 17:07.246
So what do you want?

17:07.247 --> 17:09.858
- I want my money.
- You took his money.

17:09.948 --> 17:13.458
That ain't even a long stick on a short hill
of what that mutt owes me.

17:13.548 --> 17:15.888
For one fight? So he'll pay you back.

17:15.978 --> 17:21.738
One fight? That's what he told you?
He's been sucking cash out of me for months.

17:21.828 --> 17:25.789
Sixty-tvvo K to be exact.

17:25.877 --> 17:27.768
And the way I figure it,
his debts are your debts,

17:27.769 --> 17:31.549
you being people and all.

17:31.638 --> 17:33.979
I don't have that kind of money.

17:34.069 --> 17:40.069
I'm not talking about sitting around here
for the next 40 fucking years

17:40.640 --> 17:43.160
I'm talking about a Shane Slavin comeback.

17:43.249 --> 17:46.670
(SCOFFS) You're out of your mind.

17:46.760 --> 17:48.760
I don't fight anymore.

17:48.830 --> 17:50.539
Well, you could have fooled me.

17:50.540 --> 17:53.150
Arn over here's still got a headache.

17:53.240 --> 17:56.930
With a little training, who knows?
Besides, everybody loves a comeback.

17:57.020 --> 17:59.721
No way. It's not gonna happen.

17:59.810 --> 18:01.880
That's pretty whimsical.

18:01.970 --> 18:03.500
Looky here.

18:03.501 --> 18:05.841
You fight again,
you get your brother off the hook.

18:05.931 --> 18:09.261
I make some cash, you make some cash.

18:09.350 --> 18:13.491
And your family you can't say wouldn't
be happy with a little bit of loot, right?

18:13.581 --> 18:15.380
You keep my family out of this.

18:15.381 --> 18:19.252
Now, how am I gonna do that?

18:19.341 --> 18:23.481
Everybody's rolled
into a little ball like a bunch of kittens.

18:23.571 --> 18:26.902
Are you threatening me?
Are you threatening my family?

18:26.992 --> 18:29.512
Now, that's a glass-half-empty way
of looking at it.

18:29.602 --> 18:31.581
I'm offering you a choice.

18:31.582 --> 18:34.102
You fight, or I am gonna hound,

18:34.192 --> 18:38.332
I am gonna dog your brother
right into a pine box.

18:38.422 --> 18:40.422
And don't think about
squirreling him away someplace,

18:40.492 --> 18:43.462
'cause I will get my 64K.

18:43.553 --> 18:44.991
You said 62.

18:44.992 --> 18:48.772
Yeah, well now there's a little bit of vig
for me suffering the goddamn degradation

18:48.863 --> 18:51.833
for coming down to this shithole
and talking to you.

18:51.923 --> 18:54.173
Now think about it. Get out.

18:54.263 --> 18:55.882
Start the car, Arnold.

18:55.883 --> 18:58.134
(ENGINE STARTING)

18:58.223 --> 19:00.564
He never thinks of anybody but himself!

19:00.654 --> 19:02.813
I mean, when the hell is he gonna grow up?

19:02.903 --> 19:04.973
I'm sick and tired
of all the messes he gets into.

19:05.064 --> 19:07.314
And I'm sick and tired
of taking care of him all my life.

19:07.403 --> 19:09.744
And now what?
I'm supposed to give up my life for him?

19:09.833 --> 19:14.154
We can leave.
We'll take James, we'll get out of here.

19:14.244 --> 19:16.494
- We'll lose everything.
- We'll make it.

19:16.584 --> 19:20.184
Look, Connie, I don't have
a lot of marketable skills.

19:20.274 --> 19:22.074
And I'm not going to make a living
as a grease monkey

19:22.075 --> 19:23.603
working at somebody else's place.

19:23.604 --> 19:25.494
So you wanna get beat up for a living?

19:25.495 --> 19:27.204
You saw what happened to your brother.

19:27.205 --> 19:29.455
He was stupid. He tried to cut out on Danny.

19:29.545 --> 19:31.885
They nearly killed him, Shane.

19:31.975 --> 19:35.035
Look, Con, it's just a few fights

19:35.125 --> 19:40.705
until this nightmare is over
and then we'll get our lives back.

19:40.796 --> 19:42.796
I just don't like it.

19:42.866 --> 19:44.866
Con, you never saw me fight.

19:44.936 --> 19:47.185
I was pretty good at this.

19:47.276 --> 19:50.786
But besides,
I just don't see we have any other choice.

19:50.875 --> 19:56.096
It's gotta be done.

19:56.187 --> 19:58.526
(SIGHS)

19:58.617 --> 20:04.617
DANNY G: Well, if he could've done
any better, he would've done it by now.

20:07.076 --> 20:11.217
And I want 50K, that's it,
spent on those upgrades.

20:11.307 --> 20:17.307
And don't call me at this number again
till you get it done.

20:20.037 --> 20:22.288
So what's all this?

20:22.377 --> 20:23.636
It's all for the new venue.

20:23.637 --> 20:27.508
See, things have gotten very, very, very
vanilla since you quit this business.

20:27.598 --> 20:32.998
People wanna see real brutality,
they gotta go underground.

20:33.087 --> 20:36.779
Venue changes every two weeks,
but to the world it all looks the same,

20:36.868 --> 20:42.268
streamed into my service
from Eastern Europe.

20:42.358 --> 20:43.977
Well,

20:43.978 --> 20:47.399
here you are.

20:47.489 --> 20:49.738
What, you get tired of fixing fenders?

20:49.829 --> 20:51.717
So how much do I make for each fight?

20:51.718 --> 20:55.229
Seven K each fight only if you win.

20:55.319 --> 20:57.839
So we're talking about

20:57.930 --> 20:59.458
nine fights?

20:59.459 --> 21:05.459
Only if you win.
Then again, you fix your brother's debt,

21:07.559 --> 21:10.350
I'm only doing this
till Scotty's debt is cleared.

21:10.439 --> 21:13.410
Then I'm out.

21:13.500 --> 21:17.190
Yeah, that's what they all say.

21:17.280 --> 21:19.980
So when do I get started?

21:20.070 --> 21:26.070
How about now?

21:51.662 --> 21:57.662
(SHANE GRUNTS)

21:57.782 --> 22:03.363
DANNY G: Stop it, cut it out.
You don't wanna kill him.

22:03.452 --> 22:05.251
(GROANS)

22:05.252 --> 22:07.773
This is killing me.

22:07.863 --> 22:10.472
Look, I don't know
where you've been these last two years,

22:10.563 --> 22:13.983
you've been living under a rock or something,

22:14.073 --> 22:17.313
You gotta cutout
this pansy Muay Thai dancing shit.

22:17.403 --> 22:19.924
Get with wrestling holds, judo, jujitsu.

22:20.013 --> 22:23.164
You don't understand these takedowns,
you're not gonna last one round.

22:23.254 --> 22:25.324
I don't give a fuck how quick you are.

22:25.413 --> 22:28.024
I'm a stand-up fighter, all right?
That's what I do.

22:28.114 --> 22:31.894
Stand-up?
This ain't stand-up, this is anything goes!

22:31.983 --> 22:35.313
This is head butts, this is knees, eye-gouging,

22:35.404 --> 22:37.924
punches to the groin, break your fingers.

22:38.014 --> 22:43.324
Some tvvo-ton mutt is gonna knock you down,
sit on your face, bite you on the balls,

22:43.414 --> 22:46.745
and he don't give a shit
whether it looks like bi-curious man play,

22:46.835 --> 22:47.914
you're done.

22:47.915 --> 22:52.415
And you're not gonna find
a ring doc to come in here

22:52.505 --> 22:56.375
So get with the program or get out.

22:56.465 --> 22:59.345
Now let's do it again.

22:59.435 --> 23:05.435
Shit!

23:15.905 --> 23:21.905
(GRUNTING)

23:43.897 --> 23:45.426
(GROANS)

23:45.427 --> 23:47.947
SHANE: Shit!

23:48.038 --> 23:51.547
(GRUNTS)

23:51.637 --> 23:57.637
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

24:39.880 --> 24:42.851
(SCREAMS)

24:42.940 --> 24:45.100
<i>SHANE: I'm not gonna pretend I like this.</i>

24:45.190 --> 24:50.591
<i>I resent being put in this position
and I resent being put in this position by you,</i>

24:50.681 --> 24:51.940
<i>but you're my brother,</i>

24:51.941 --> 24:56.531
<i>and I'm doing it
because I think it's the right thing to do.</i>

24:56.621 --> 24:59.321
<i>But you screw up once and you're out.</i>

24:59.411 --> 25:01.390
<i>I catch you doing drugs, you're out.</i>

25:01.391 --> 25:03.912
<i>I catch you selling drugs, you're out.</i>

25:04.001 --> 25:06.161
<i>I catch you bringing girls in or making bets</i>

