01:00:54.747 --> 01:00:56.747
Hey!

01:00:56.817 --> 01:00:57.986
Hey!

01:00:57.987 --> 01:01:00.147
Stop! Get him off me!

01:01:00.237 --> 01:01:03.388
DANNY G: Get him! Bring his ass out here.

01:01:03.477 --> 01:01:06.988
Listen, you. I know where you live.

01:01:07.078 --> 01:01:09.148
I know where your wife lives.

01:01:09.238 --> 01:01:11.578
I know where that brat of yours
goes to school.

01:01:11.668 --> 01:01:14.637
(GRUNTS)

01:01:14.728 --> 01:01:17.338
I asked you to lose and make it look real,

01:01:17.428 --> 01:01:20.758
not roll over
like some goddamn wet Chihuahua.

01:01:20.849 --> 01:01:23.548
How can I make this look real?

01:01:23.639 --> 01:01:27.419
I'm tired of getting the crap kicked out of me
for nothing by guys who can't even fight!

01:01:27.508 --> 01:01:29.308
You want real? I'll give you real.

01:01:29.309 --> 01:01:32.189
Stand him up.

01:01:32.279 --> 01:01:33.898
I just want out of this.

01:01:33.899 --> 01:01:35.787
You will be soon enough out of it,

01:01:35.788 --> 01:01:38.219
now get your ass back out there and fight.

01:01:38.309 --> 01:01:43.349
What are you talking about?
I've already fought tonight.

01:01:43.439 --> 01:01:46.410
Now get your ass out there! Get him out there.

01:01:46.500 --> 01:01:52.500
Get him out there!

01:01:53.700 --> 01:01:56.220
- That one, too.
- Okay, are you okay?

01:01:56.310 --> 01:01:57.929
(SCOTTY GROANING)

01:01:57.930 --> 01:01:59.009
There you go.

01:01:59.010 --> 01:02:00.449
(SCOTTY CHUCKLES)

01:02:00.450 --> 01:02:04.681
Thanks.

01:02:04.770 --> 01:02:06.569
Oof!

01:02:06.570 --> 01:02:08.910
Feels good to have this back again, huh?

01:02:09.000 --> 01:02:10.800
Be back in the ring in no time.

01:02:10.801 --> 01:02:14.581
Knock those guys out, take them all down.

01:02:14.671 --> 01:02:19.981
Hey, you okay?

01:02:20.072 --> 01:02:22.502
I just don't get it.

01:02:22.591 --> 01:02:25.742
It's like he's a whole new person.

01:02:25.832 --> 01:02:29.972
I mean, I know he's incredibly frustrated
and he's worried about money, but...

01:02:30.061 --> 01:02:33.122
It's notjust that, though, Con.

01:02:33.212 --> 01:02:34.291
What do you mean?

01:02:34.292 --> 01:02:36.722
Well, the money's big, yeah.

01:02:36.812 --> 01:02:40.052
But taking dives? It's not easy.

01:02:40.142 --> 01:02:42.752
But you gotta understand.

01:02:42.843 --> 01:02:45.452
Danny has this way

01:02:45.542 --> 01:02:48.422
of making you feel special, you know?

01:02:48.513 --> 01:02:50.583
You know, I remember when I first started,

01:02:50.673 --> 01:02:54.902
he was like this
weird kind of father figure to me...

01:02:54.993 --> 01:02:58.593
I mean, you were young.

01:02:58.683 --> 01:03:01.203
It's probably even worse for Shane,
you know?

01:03:01.293 --> 01:03:03.293
I mean, after our parents split,

01:03:03.363 --> 01:03:04.982
he didn't have that father figure,

01:03:04.983 --> 01:03:10.983
so it must've been nice
having someone watching his back,

01:03:11.553 --> 01:03:16.324
But anyway, Connie, this isn't your fault.

01:03:16.414 --> 01:03:20.014
Hey, you and Shane wouldn't even
be in this position if it wasn't for me.

01:03:20.104 --> 01:03:23.974
Yeah? If I hadn't screwed up so bad.

01:03:24.064 --> 01:03:26.064
Look, we're a family now,

01:03:26.134 --> 01:03:28.654
and we'll get through this as a family.

01:03:28.745 --> 01:03:30.273
YOU think?

01:03:30.274 --> 01:03:32.345
I know.

01:03:32.435 --> 01:03:38.435
All right? Whatever it takes.

01:03:43.235 --> 01:03:47.735
<i>And now Shane Slavin</i>

01:03:47.826 --> 01:03:51.156
<i>versus Joe Sanboon!</i>

01:03:51.245 --> 01:03:57.245
Come on, guys, fight!

01:04:27.248 --> 01:04:33.248
(TALKS INDISTINCTLY)

01:04:51.008 --> 01:04:57.008
(CROWD CHANTING) Fight! Fight! Fight!

01:05:54.371 --> 01:05:56.622
Now, that looked real.

01:05:56.712 --> 01:06:02.712
Stick him in his car.

01:06:10.212 --> 01:06:14.893
Scotty? Scotty.

01:06:14.982 --> 01:06:16.982
SCOTTY: Okay, hold on.

01:06:17.052 --> 01:06:21.823
CONNIE: I'm gonna go and look for him, and
you're gonna stay here and look after James.

01:06:21.913 --> 01:06:23.532
- I'm gonna go.
- Shane never came home?

01:06:23.533 --> 01:06:24.883
No, I'm gonna go look...

01:06:24.884 --> 01:06:29.203
Yeah, all right, all right. What, uh...

01:06:29.293 --> 01:06:30.553
- Yeah.
- Okay.

01:06:30.554 --> 01:06:32.554
(STAMMERING) S0...

01:06:32.624 --> 01:06:34.512
- All right, you need to take him to school.
- Yeah.

01:06:34.513 --> 01:06:37.034
Okay, I'll go... I'll go, you stay here.

01:06:37.124 --> 01:06:42.884
- All right. Okay, don't worry, don't worry.
- You call me.

01:06:42.974 --> 01:06:48.015
- Okay.
- All right?

01:06:48.105 --> 01:06:50.624
(MUMBLING)

01:06:50.714 --> 01:06:52.244
DRIVER: Hey, you sure
you know where we're going?

01:06:52.245 --> 01:06:55.755
I know where I'm going, man,
just keep driving.

01:06:55.845 --> 01:07:01.845
All right, let's go all the way to the top.

01:07:04.935 --> 01:07:08.806
Around here.

01:07:08.895 --> 01:07:14.566
Follow this all the way down,
then take a right.

01:07:14.655 --> 01:07:20.655
Okay, go, go! There, there, there!
Go to that car there!

01:07:21.136 --> 01:07:22.755
Okay, stop, stop, stop.

01:07:22.756 --> 01:07:28.756
Here you go, man.

01:07:33.107 --> 01:07:39.107
Oh. Damn it! Shane.

01:07:39.227 --> 01:07:43.007
Shane? Shane!

01:07:43.097 --> 01:07:46.427
Get off of me.

01:07:46.517 --> 01:07:48.517
I don't need you! I don't need anybody!

01:07:48.587 --> 01:07:50.567
The hell you don't! Christ!

01:07:50.568 --> 01:07:55.518
Where are your keys so I can drive you home?

01:07:55.608 --> 01:07:57.767
Jesus Christ.

01:07:57.858 --> 01:08:00.197
Look at you. We need to clean you up a bit.

01:08:00.288 --> 01:08:01.997
(SHANE GROANS)

01:08:01.998 --> 01:08:03.707
Man.

01:08:03.708 --> 01:08:06.048
I can't believe you ended up here.

01:08:06.138 --> 01:08:10.998
I haven't been to this spot in years, man.

01:08:11.088 --> 01:08:13.158
Hey, you remember when we used to

01:08:13.248 --> 01:08:16.129
catch live fish off the dock here
back in the day?

01:08:16.219 --> 01:08:18.198
I used to catch the fish.

01:08:18.198 --> 01:08:21.169
Everything's a fucking competition
with you, huh?

01:08:21.259 --> 01:08:24.859
- What are you doing here, anyway?
- I'm saving your ass.

01:08:24.948 --> 01:08:27.470
I'm gonna drive you home to your family.

01:08:27.559 --> 01:08:30.618
I'm only here because of you, anyway.

01:08:30.710 --> 01:08:33.859
Don't start, Shane. Dumbass.

01:08:33.948 --> 01:08:35.749
God damn it.

01:08:35.750 --> 01:08:37.639
(SHANE GROANS)

01:08:37.640 --> 01:08:39.710
They got you real bad, huh?

01:08:39.800 --> 01:08:45.800
Yeah. Whose fault was that?

01:08:52.399 --> 01:08:56.451
Shane, you ready?
She's gonna be home soon.

01:08:56.540 --> 01:08:59.781
Hey.

01:08:59.870 --> 01:09:02.571
Hey, sweetie.

01:09:02.661 --> 01:09:05.541
My God, Shane.

01:09:05.631 --> 01:09:11.631
Daddy, are you all right?

01:09:13.551 --> 01:09:15.170
SHANE: What the hell happened to you?

01:09:15.171 --> 01:09:18.682
It's just he got in a fight
with those boys at school.

01:09:18.772 --> 01:09:20.661
Stop, you're scaring him!

01:09:20.662 --> 01:09:22.551
- It's just he got...
- He just what?

01:09:22.551 --> 01:09:27.682
Got the crap kicked out of him?

01:09:27.772 --> 01:09:29.571
It's all right, sweetheart.

01:09:29.572 --> 01:09:31.461
This is your fault.

01:09:31.462 --> 01:09:32.631
What?

01:09:32.631 --> 01:09:35.602
He never got into fights
before you came around.

01:09:35.693 --> 01:09:38.482
Is this what you've been doing?
Teaching him to fight?

01:09:38.573 --> 01:09:41.002
I mean when you're not too busy
sneaking around hitting on my wife.

01:09:41.093 --> 01:09:42.171
Shane!

01:09:42.173 --> 01:09:44.783
- Hitting on your wife? Are you insane?
- CONNIE: In your room now.

01:09:44.872 --> 01:09:45.952
Go to your room now.

01:09:45.953 --> 01:09:49.193
I took you into my home,
the stupidest thing I've ever done,

01:09:49.283 --> 01:09:50.812
and this is how you pay me back?

01:09:50.813 --> 01:09:53.154
Are you kidding me?
I don't know what you're thinking.

01:09:53.243 --> 01:09:54.863
You wanna know what I'm thinking?

01:09:54.864 --> 01:09:59.724
While I'm busy fighting your battles for you,

01:09:59.814 --> 01:10:04.134
Sucking up to my son, sucking up to my wife,
pretending like this is your home.

01:10:04.224 --> 01:10:08.274
Well, it's not.

01:10:08.364 --> 01:10:11.065
- Shane, no.
- You stay out of this.

01:10:11.154 --> 01:10:13.224
SHANE: I took you in, I took care of you,

01:10:13.314 --> 01:10:15.925
and I told you this is the last time

01:10:16.015 --> 01:10:17.634
(BREATH ES H EAVILY)

01:10:17.635 --> 01:10:19.073
or I'm done.

01:10:19.074 --> 01:10:22.765
I don't care anymore,
and I want you out of my house now.

01:10:22.855 --> 01:10:25.555
- Shane, no.
- SCOTTY: No, Connie.

01:10:25.645 --> 01:10:28.886
Connie, it's okay, he's right.

01:10:28.975 --> 01:10:31.405
You're right.
I should've never let this happen.

01:10:31.495 --> 01:10:33.655
I shouldn't have stayed so long.

01:10:33.746 --> 01:10:38.336
But you know what?
ljust got used to being part of it, okay?

01:10:38.425 --> 01:10:40.225
All right, so I'm sorry.

01:10:40.226 --> 01:10:41.754
- Scotty, please.
- It's okay, Connie.

01:10:41.755 --> 01:10:44.726
SHANE: Leave him alone.

01:10:44.816 --> 01:10:45.985
Scotty, please don't go.

01:10:45.986 --> 01:10:47.425
SCOTTY: Connie, it's okay, really.

01:10:47.426 --> 01:10:50.397
- Just let him go.
- SCOTTY: It's cool.

01:10:50.486 --> 01:10:52.466
SCOTTY: N0, but thank you.

01:10:52.467 --> 01:10:54.537
You know, for taking me in
and trying to straighten me out.

01:10:54.626 --> 01:10:57.956
You know, maybe one day
I could return the favor and...

01:10:58.046 --> 01:11:04.046
Yeah, what are the chances of that, huh?

01:11:12.087 --> 01:11:15.867
Give me a break.

01:11:15.958 --> 01:11:18.118
- What?
- CONNIE: Are you happy?

01:11:18.207 --> 01:11:19.737
You know, for your information,

01:11:19.738 --> 01:11:23.518
it was you who gave James the idea
he should stick up for himself, not Scotty.

01:11:23.607 --> 01:11:25.497
- What are you talking about?
- Yeah, you.

01:11:25.498 --> 01:11:27.928
And you're the one
who told him not to be a crybaby.

01:11:28.018 --> 01:11:31.258
And you're the one
who didn't even bother to look at his project.

01:11:31.348 --> 01:11:34.498
You know he built that thing
to make his daddy proud?

01:11:34.588 --> 01:11:39.269
And when that failed, he got into a fight
to make his daddy proud.

01:11:39.358 --> 01:11:41.789
- He told you that?
- He didn't have to.

01:11:41.878 --> 01:11:44.669
Shane, don't you get it?

01:11:44.758 --> 01:11:48.629
This isn't Scotty's fault, this is our fault.

01:11:48.719 --> 01:11:49.888
I mean...

01:11:49.889 --> 01:11:51.418
- Connie, I'm sorry...
- No!

01:11:51.419 --> 01:11:54.389
Whatever you have to say,

01:11:54.479 --> 01:11:57.450
say it to your son.

01:11:57.540 --> 01:12:01.769
I will always be here, but your son?

01:12:01.860 --> 01:12:07.860
You need to talk to him right now.

01:12:16.441 --> 01:12:20.490
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

01:12:20.581 --> 01:12:23.821
(SIGHS)

01:12:23.911 --> 01:12:26.701
Hey, buddy.

01:12:26.791 --> 01:12:32.791
You Okay?

01:12:39.481 --> 01:12:42.992
I am really sorry, okay?

01:12:43.082 --> 01:12:46.412
You know, you didn't do anything wrong.

01:12:46.502 --> 01:12:48.842
I've just been going through some...

01:12:48.932 --> 01:12:53.252
This crazy adult stuff, you know?

01:12:53.342 --> 01:12:57.033
I was completely out of line.

01:12:57.123 --> 01:13:00.272
S0 I'm really sorry.

01:13:00.363 --> 01:13:02.342
You know I love you, right?

01:13:02.343 --> 01:13:03.692
Okay.

01:13:03.693 --> 01:13:05.131
I love you more than anything.

01:13:05.132 --> 01:13:11.132
JAMES: I love you, too.

01:14:13.086 --> 01:14:17.857
I'm gonna look for Scotty.

01:14:17.947 --> 01:14:21.547
I think I owe him an apology.

01:14:21.637 --> 01:14:27.637
That's what I've been trying to tell you.

01:15:43.000 --> 01:15:44.890
Hey, Danny.

01:15:44.891 --> 01:15:46.689
Hiya, kid.

01:15:46.690 --> 01:15:49.661
Look, ljust came
to square up with you, okay?

01:15:49.751 --> 01:15:52.811
Too late for that.

01:15:52.901 --> 01:15:54.700
No, it's not too late.

01:15:54.701 --> 01:15:57.041
I still owe you that 30 grand, remember?

01:15:57.131 --> 01:16:01.181
Turns out your brother's a real goldmine,
so your 30 grand

01:16:01.271 --> 01:16:05.502
it don't cut no ice with me.

01:16:05.592 --> 01:16:07.390
I'm...

01:16:07.391 --> 01:16:11.081
What are you saying,
you're gonna leave us alone now?

01:16:11.172 --> 01:16:13.332
That we're good, we're done?

01:16:13.422 --> 01:16:15.041
We're not done.

01:16:15.042 --> 01:16:17.653
You cross me, you hurt my feelings.

01:16:17.742 --> 01:16:20.173
You hurt my feelings, you hurt my reputation.

01:16:20.262 --> 01:16:24.852
"My reputation, my reputation.
Oh, my reputation."

01:16:24.943 --> 01:16:27.913
You know who said that?

01:16:28.003 --> 01:16:29.982
No.

01:16:29.983 --> 01:16:35.983
Some mutt named Cassio
in an old limey play about a schvartze.

01:17:04.815 --> 01:17:07.064
(GUN COCKS)

01:17:07.155 --> 01:17:13.155
Now we're done.

01:17:14.085 --> 01:17:20.085
CONNIE: Well?

01:17:21.466 --> 01:17:23.355
I'll look again in the morning

